how do u get all forms of burmy burmy what appears on first glance to be your standard bug pok mon that is only obtainable on trees however burmy has a difference that very few others have it changes its form this form difference is not based on the game version or weather this pok mon's form changes entirely on where it last battled however this does bring in interesting factoids about it when the female version evolves when a female burmy evolves at lv it keeps the form it was in when it evolved grass form the more commonly seen form of burmy you will see is the grass form this form appears when you battle wild pok mon or trainers in grass forests or just general green areas when it evolves into minomadammu this form of wormadam gains the grass type which adds to its weaknesses it has a different moveset to the others ground form the next burmy form is the yellow ground form this form is obtained after battling in caves ruins or on roads when it evolves into minomadammu this form of wormadam gains the ground type which adds to its weaknesses it has a different moveset to the others steel form the next burmy form is the pink steel form this form is obtained after battling inside buildings when it evolves into minomadammu this form of wormadam gains the steel type which adds to its weaknesses it has a different moveset to the others Pok__mon types Pok__mon Trading Card Game Missingno. Pok__mon Pok__mon (video games) Pok__mon Emerald Pok__mon Ruby and Sapphire Lairon Pok__mon Yellow Pok__mon Colosseum Bulbasaur Pok__mon Red and Blue Pok__mon Gold and Silver Deoxys Aggron Venusaur Pok__mon FireRed and LeafGreen 'M Celebi Pok__dex Gengar Venonat May (Pok__mon) Parasect Scyther Cloyster Eevee Pikachu Battle Frontier Smeargle Orre Skarmory Crobat Pok__mon evolution Donphan Sceptile Pok__mon XD: Gale of Darkness Pidgeotto Hypno Pok__mon (anime) Ivysaur Aipom Ekans Weedle Metapod Umbreon Abra (Pok__mon) Wurmple Rhydon Delibird Steelix Pok__mon Adventures Heracross Pok__mon